<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-338-399  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 338 399.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Office  Jan 1989 v109 n1 p46(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Information tracking: an idea whose software has come. (Focus onSoftware) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Whitmyer, Claude F.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information tracking packages are designed to make it easy for theuser to keep track of information that is important to daily work.andO;Text-retrieval software is one type of information trackingsoftware.andP;  It is designed to provide precise answers in a shorttime to questions users may have about the data they are currentlyworking on.andP;  This data includes informal data, formal data,writing support and correspondence.andP;  Most text-retrieval packagesrequire users to convert their files to a format that they canhandle.andP;  Microlytics Inc's Gofer software, a RAM-resident packagethat can search an entire hard disk for key words and phrases, isdesigned for users that need to search data that changes often.andO;The packages AskSam, Memory Mate, Zyindex 2.20, Ize, Dayflo'sTracker and Minds 2.3 are designed for static needs, and requireindexing before searching.andP;  Other text-retrieval packages are alsodiscussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Software PackagesTracking SystemsInformation Storage and RetrievalText Communication.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>